scene_description: the background is made of grey pixels. black pixels form a series of right angles, made up of units of 4 black pixels in the shape of a square. each unit can only be placed upon another unit, except for the ones at the base of the grid. there are 7 units of black squares, composed of 4 pixels, on the base layer, starting from the left side of the grid. on the layer above that, which is the 3rd and 4th row from the bottom, there are 6 units of black squares, again starting from the left. this continues until the top layer, which has 1 unit of 4 black pixels in the shape of a square, in the 3rd and 4th row from the top. on this large shape made of these units there are orange pixels that form lines of varying shapes, made of 3 pixels.
literal_instruction: several different orange pixels will be removed. to do so, replace the selected orange pixels with grey pixels. first, remove all of the orange pixels in the 1st column from the left except for the one in the first row from the bottom. then, remove the orange pixel in the 6th column from the left. remove all of the orange pixels that are to the left of the 6th column from the left. next, add orange pixels to the grid, replacing grey pixels. in the 5th column from the left, add a pixel in the 7th row from the bottom. then, in the 8th column from the left, add an orange pixel to the 7th and 8th row from the top. finally, add an orange pixel in the 7th column from the left in the 6th row from the top. good job.
